<br>
<br>
~Sisters,<br>
My tribe has gone to war against an evil known as the Saurians. They have attacked children attending XenaVerse High, they have attempted to conquer our Allies in Rome, they also have been killing the Ancient Tribe of the Odusians, Amazon Children of the Ancients. I seek assistance from my fellow sister tribes. This is a battle that will not be easilly won. Currently, they keep Eli of the Elisians captive, but I do not know how long they will allow him to live. Only come if you know you can be of service, I will not be responsible for the deaths of my athelfi. This is a greater enemy than the Centaurs ever could be. Come if you can to Scynthia.~<br>
<br>
- Queen Alysia Lillian Loire -<br>
<br>
<br>
(Note: The battles are taking place on the AotNL Ezboard)  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=queenpallas>QueenPallas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#993300>(8/18/01 2:07:14 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Seeing the war scroll</span><hr size=1> Queen Pallas looked at Kel with sorrowful eyes. <br>
<br>
&quot;It is definately a pity... the war. Will you go to battle,&quot; Kel asked Pallas.<br>
<br>
&quot;I'm afraid not. I must keep my loyal promise to the Goddesses Athena and Artemis, that the only wars that I shall endure, are the wars of defense. It is a pity though. Our lives, they are filled with violence and war. We shall live in peace and harmony. Amazons of a different sort. No, no I don't think I shall battle along side my sister Alysia of Scynthia. I pray her outcome favors her... and I wish her the best,&quot; Queen Pallas voiced.<br>
<br>
&quot;As do I,&quot; Kel returned.<br>
<br>
&quot;Alysia is an Amazon of the Northern Lands... lets also bid Artemis that those Amazons are taken care of, and proclaimed victors of the horrific war,&quot; said Queen Pallas.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yes, my Queen... I pray that the Amazons of the Northern Lands be victors in this war,&quot; Kel returned. <br>
<br>
Queen Pallas and Kel began to help their tribe gather food. Today, they were going to honor the Goddesses. Kel again pressed Pallas for children. Pallas only laughed and continued to hunt with the others. Kel angered looked at Pallas and thought...  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   this is the woman I married. Shaking her head, she too joined Pallas in the hunt. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ueiliethyia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eiliethyia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(8/18/01 6:03:40 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> children?</span><hr size=1> As if by a call, a small toddler appeared not far from the hunt.  Curly blonde locks around her face and the icy blue eyes of her mother, she giggled as she watched the amazon named Kel.  The little goddess had heared her wishes.  Her own mother Hera had been to busy recently to catch all the wishes for children.  So, the little one had already begun to bless the mortals with her presence.<br>
Little Eiliethyia couldn't much talk.  But, her powers were already growing.  She winked as best she could at Kel.  Giving the amazon the power...but only this once...to have a child with her lover.   But, it would be when they both wished it.  <br>
Then with another little giggle, Eiliethyia dissappeared back to Mount Olympus to find her mother. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=queenpallas>QueenPallas</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#993300>(8/23/01 4:48:42 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Queen Pallas Thanks the Child.</span><hr size=1> Kel, not believing what she had seen smiled at the child. She looked at Pallas. &quot;I think we've been blessed... could it have been Eiliethyia? Oh please Pallas... shall we have a child,&quot; Kel pleaded.<br>
<br>
Queen Pallas smiled... &quot;in due time. With her head bowed towards where the child was once present... Queen Pallas thanked Eiliethyia.&quot;<br>
<br>
Kel embraced Queen Pallas tighter, at the thought of them creating a life together. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.showPrevMessage?topicID=12.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.showNextMessage?topicID=12.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.emailToFriend?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.threadControl?topicID=12.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/deleteThreadFire.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm30.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=12.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub11.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="amazonsuniteamazonsunitescrollboard">Amazons Unite Scroll Board<option value="amazonsunitefrm39">Guild Applications<option value="amazonsunitefrm37">The Mythical Odyssey Forum<option value="amazonsunitefrm23">The Olympian Gods<option value="amazonsunitefrm15">Black Sea Tavern and Inn<option value="amazonsunitefrm32">The Mythical Odyssey<option value="amazonsunitefrm35">Amazon Nation Alliance<option value="amazo